Subject A Song~
Text
Greetings again,

By the request of Lady Lilisa, I have composed a song that I feel embodies
the essence of the Coven.  While contemplating this piece, I was forced to
strip the..  Ambitions of your Halls down to their grandest purpose, which I
feel is the pursuit of knowledge.  I believe this concept is stressed in the
song, as is my desire for said knowledge.  I hope you all enjoy.  

===========================================================================

Past marvelous courtyards of blackened stone,
Down aged walkways where echoes moan,
Are ancient Halls of which few know:
The Coven of the Shunned, set far below.

A child\@s scream is no strange sound,
For here virgin blood does abound.
Since age does taint the natural wine,
A child\@s blood\@s far more divine.

And such a sight as Demonkind,
Ripping bodies clear in twine,
The Covenites have seen before,
And very well may see once more.

Forbidden secrets time has buried deep,
The Covenites do diligently seek.
To peek beyond that sacred Veil,
To see just what can be revealed.

Making pacts with Demonkind,
They seek their knowledge to refine.
And in their everlasting task,
In the darkness of it bask.

Ambition spurs them further still:
They gladly carry out the Dark Gods\@ will.
For given them is something grand:
Knowledge, even from Heavenly hands.

And \@gainst ones who would them control,
They rebel against the fitted mold.
Instead they fight with all their might,
Destroying those blinded by the Light.

To reside in Halls such as this,
It is, indeed, my whole-hearted wish.
And so with You I wish to conspire,
For me, I know, You shall Inspire.

===========================================================================

I do hope I hear word from you soon.

-Iljodiya Hven\@Ilyast
~
