Subject Visions of my past.~
Text
For long I have lived in the cities, thinking that there I would find the
answers to my past.  But Tachja has forced me to return to my old home,
though I seem to be able to recall little of it.  After stopping and
resting, my mind seemed to clear a little...  My thoughts run on other
tracks than advancement and equipment.  Soon a vision of my past presented
itself to me, that of a great Wolf spirit.  I know not why I remember it,
nor what it did, but I felt at peace thinking of it.  I realized that my
time in the cities and fortresses had dulled my sense of Nature, had robbed
me of the life I should have led.  

I fear I am not the strongest of warriors, nor the mightiest of mages.  I am
ashamed that I am not even the bravest of adventurers, but even with all my
faults I honestly believe your path to be the True one.  I do not ask you to
accept me into the Pack, for I know I am not strong enough to become one of
your hunters.  But I do ask that you see my heart for what truly lies in it
and know that I follow you, whether or not you think me worthy to be a
champion of your cause.  


Hunt well, and think upon what I have said.
Rushnak
~
