Subject The Enlightenment.~
Text
Lord Rveyelhi,

Father in blood, patron of sin, I call upon you in order that I might
receive your grace.  Yes, liege, your grace to continue on this narrow road
that has revealed itself to me in the sanguine visions that come to me in
the darkest hours of the night.  By your leave, I would set into motion
plans that have not been attempted for ages past.  

I speak of course, of the inscription and encantation of unions so old as to
be almost entirely forgotten by the minds of mortal creatures.  The rise of
the Lords of Order -- the Lords of Dominion.  For the last two decades, I
have carried out your will as your own crushing fist.  As I have bathed in
the blood of Our enemies, new understanding and order has come into my mind.


My very being has been bombarded with the knowledge of things that I should
know nothing about, but that I do indeed know of.  As this information has
taken form in my mind, so has a new clarity presented itself to me.  In my
visions, I have come to know what might be, and what must be done to assure
such an end.  So again, I ask for your grace.  

I have witnessed as the primal matter was shaped inside the void of
nothingness that was.  How chaos ensued in the creation -- how Lord Iandir\@s
will laced the entity with the same void that was, and is, and will be,
bringing his Order unto the world.  Again, I have witnessed this, and more. 
I saw in my visions the abstraction that began to take shape.  Cities built,
the Lord\@s laws decreed.  Naturally, I revel in this enlightenment.  

As a boy, I escaped the undercity one step ahead of my own execution.  At
the time, I did not understand as I do now.  I did not Know.  But now I can
see that new abstractions can arise.  The new structure to give the order
that existed in the beginning.  My vision is of the expansion of the law\@s
rule to the corner of the worlds.  But more than that -- the exertion of
dominion over the populace.  

As a Guardian of Law, I have watched as we have waxed and waned in the
authority and councils of men.  Our pure cause sometimes preferred by the
fools, and sometimes not.  I have witnessed our own limitations.  Through my
visions, it has been made clear how such can be transcended.  It is for
this, of course, that I ask your grace.  I speak of the configuration of
thrones, and the nine phrases of dominion.  I speak of destruction, and of
creation.  

The alatharyans uttered the phrases from their pyramids -- the pyramids
themselves forming the crests that represented the thirteen great lords of
the void.  Their way was folly, because they did what they dared with minds
that were not perfectly ordered.  And so they failed, and were smited for
their insolence.  At this time, we do not of course have the means to invoke
the configuration as mightily as the alatharyans did -- but it can still be
invoked, in the lesser form.  

Jidriln has begun to see matters in the same light as I, as his mind grows
more ordered with the passing of time, and the spilling of blood.  He has
agreed to join me in this endeavor, if our respective Lords agree to its
doing.  If that be the case, then we would utter the phrases, and begin the
journey that would end in the domination of the world to the purpose of
order.  

We would transcend our forms to become more than dead, and less than living,
but wholly pure in the organized states of our minds.  We would become
golems of law, golems of void.  And then the world would know us, and they
would know the enlightenment of the age that we bring unto them.  So, by
your grace, I would continue upon this path.  

Biezkul Yv\@Piki,
Fist of Rveyelhi,
Guardian Leader of Var Bandor
~
