Text
What I seek is a means to an end.  That means is the title of a Raider of Twilight.  
The end is to acquire that which I want.  Nothing less.  I see something, I take it.  I 
have been over this land, preying on those around me with exquisite hunger.  I 
have become strong, but my hunger has not be satiated.  The things I seek, the 
Raiders of Twilight cannot give me.  But joining your ranks will be a means to 
these things.  Already I hear whispers in my wake, already they watch me.  I want 
them to grovel in fear.  I want to feed on this fear and all that comes with it.  What I 
see I make my own.  And my sights are now set on your House.  I do not come to 
you begging and I do not expect you to simply allow me to walk in.  Give me a 
chance to prove myself and I will show you how my name will be remembered.  
The cities shall tremble at the whisper of my passing.  The walls shall crumble at 
our pillaging.  With the acceptance of me within your ranks I can bring many eager 
young candidates, young men and women who will gladly throw their lot in for the 
power that they shall gather.  I shall spread your name and they will come.  
Together we can overcome the pathetic forces of Law that run rampant on this 
world.  They believe themselves safe within their cities.  Within their laws.  Their 
cities are mine.  Their laws, I shall rewrite.

Gahnix Etzyaq
~
