Subject Dishonor~
Text
I write this scroll to make you aware of the taint one of yours has put
upon you.  I do this, not because I believe in the ways that you require,
but because I believe in the teachings of my Goddess, the Windwolf, with
every ounce of strength within my body, and soul.  This is the very same
reason that Salmik and I have bonded, in the past.  And this is the reason
that I called upon him to resolve the situation at hand.  But no resolution
was offered, as Gahnak, the offender refused even Salmiks resolution.  

The offense, Dolgrael, is so sharply in contrast to your own teachings, that
I think even the reading of this scroll will pain you.  After battles had
raged, me, protecting my brethern who he attacked underhandedly, as my
brother travelled, exploring the realms, and was weakened, we arrived at a
stand-still, each having won, but not completed, two to three attempts at
the others life.  It was here that we decided one more battle was at hand,
even after he had voiced doubt in his own ability to win such a duel, and
offered me escape.  

At the onset of this battle, we made standards, that no one elses magics
would enchant us, as he had been using the aid of a fire scholar and I, the
spells of a water templar.  I stepped west, away from the guards, to wait
for him, and quaffed a potion, which had not been set outside the boundaries
of the battle, and which he had also drank from.  It was here that the
standards were broken.  Gahnak asked Anaelis to provide him spells, and
Anaelis did.  

In the end, I fell.  This does not injure me as much as my loss of respect,
and my complete bafflement at the happenings.  Nor does it harm me as much
as did attempting to relieve these injustices in front of a crowd, who
considered my snivveling, despite that I only sought to do you, Dolgrael,
dignity, by untarnishing the reputation of one who values integrity as I do.


Finally, if you would care to call upon witnesses, you might ask Anaelis,
Kukir, Gathorn or Inthyssn.  

Tachja Kotrormund 
~
