Subject *a tear-stained parchment*~
Text
As I look back on the time I have spent with you...  I can only think of
the abuse I've suffered.  The doubts cast relentlessly in my direction, the
twisting of my heart in so many hands.  

And I have said to myself, 'no, this doesn't matter, for that I care for
him'.  

And I have looked upon the times I have spent with you, and I think...  Of
how you have treated me.  

Perhaps you do not realize the effects your words would have upon someone
such as myself.  Perhaps it does not occur to you the sheer undermining of
confidence that is implicit in such phrases as 'I could not put you into
that kind of danger'.  The blows you dealt to me with phrases such as 'I
couldn't bear to see you get hurt.  ' 

The sheer lack of respect for anything I might do that rang through those
words.  I would rather you had slapped me.  

Even now, I stand...  Terrified.  Awash in the realization that I -have-
come as far as I have, relying upon you.  And the terror arises in me that I
am not strong enough to stand alone.  

The terror that would never have existed in me, before I had heard such
phrases.  

The condesencion in the phrase you said to me, 'I know you are a fierce
warrior'.  

And I would have said to myself...  'This doesn't matter, for that I care
for him'.  

And I do care for you, for all the pains you have dealt me.  

But I can't throw myself into a fire for forever.  I can't keep doing that
and hope that this time, the fire won't burn.  

I can't keep doing this to myself.  

What am I throwing myself at you for?  To be placed upon a pedestal, turned
once more into some blown-glass doll?  

Throwing myself into anguish to receive more anguish?  I can't do this.  

I don't believe I'll be troubling you further, Raelasu.  

I love you more than anything I've loved in this world, but this sort of
pain...  Is too much.  

But I will always love you.  

Tyira Moilsya 
~
